Project Management Component Documentation
Overview
The ProjectManagement component is responsible for managing a project's tasks across different stages represented by columns: To Do, In Progress, and Done. It provides functionality to add, edit, and delete tasks, as well as drag-and-drop functionality for moving tasks between columns.

Functionality
Add Card
Allows users to add a new task card to the selected column.
Validates the title and description of the new task before adding it.
Opens a modal dialog for entering the task details.
Edit Card
Enables users to edit the details of an existing task card.
Opens a modal dialog pre-filled with the selected task's details for editing.
Validates the updated title and description before saving changes.
Delete Card
Provides an option to delete a task card from the project.
Prompts the user for confirmation before permanently removing the task.
Drag-and-Drop
Implements drag-and-drop functionality for moving task cards between columns.
Updates the task card's position and column when dropped into a new column.
Design Approach
Component Structure
Utilizes React functional components and hooks for state management.
Organizes tasks into columns within a flexible grid layout.
State Management
Utilizes React's useState and useEffect hooks for managing component state.
Stores column and task data in the component's state, synchronized with local storage.
User Interface
Employs Bootstrap for responsive and visually appealing UI components.
Enhances user experience with modal dialogs for adding and editing task details.
Drag-and-Drop Implementation
Implements HTML5 drag-and-drop API for intuitive task management.
Handles drag start, drag over, and drop events to update task positions.
